Text:
for all you people whining about seeders:

1) Cap your upload speed.  I know it sounds crazy, but chances are, you are on an ADSL connection, and ADSL download speed gets crippled when you are uploading too fast.  Cap your upload speed to 75% of max, and you should be able to download at 100% max speed.  If you are uploading at 100% max, you can only download at 10%.  

2) Wait.  It's a 15GB game, it's brand new, and it's very popular.  So it's going to take AT LEAST 24 hours to download for most people, if not more.  Whining about seeders is NOT going to help; if people are refusing to seed, then seeing your whiny comments are NOT going to change their minds!  People ARE seeding.  If you can't connect to them, it's your fault!
